_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) some of th=
e industry=E2=80=99s top costume designers=E2=80=94including Loewe=E2=80=99=
s Jonathan Anderson, the stylist visionary behind the looks in Luca Guadagn=
ino=E2=80=99s Challengers and Queer=E2=80=94about the precision and intelle=
ct that goes into the aesthetic tapestry of filmmaking. The great Baratunde=
 Thurston chatted=20
( https://puck.news/filmmakers-behind-the-years-best-documentaries-talk-sto=
ry-craft/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2811%2F23%2F24%29&utm=
_content=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2811%2F16%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demai=
l_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) with the =
season=E2=80=99s top documentarians about the backstories undergirding thei=
r work. (I was particularly interested in the commentary from Morgan Nevill=
e, whose Piece by Piece I had just watched with my family a few nights earl=
ier, and Matt Tyrnauer, the acclaimed director behind Carville: Winning Is =
Everything, Stupid. More than 20 years ago, Matt was my boss when I interne=
d at Vanity Fair.)

Meanwhile, Peter Hamby helmed a starry panel featuring Zoe Salda=C3=B1a, Pe=
ter Sarsgaard, and Jeremy Strong, three leading acting-awards contenders th=
is season. Strong, who stars as a young Roy Cohn in The Apprentice, was par=
ticularly poignant onstage. And I was thrilled to hear him explain his proc=
ess while standing beside Gabe Sherman, my old
friend and the film=E2=80=99s screenwriter and producer. I fondly remembere=
d Gabe=E2=80=99s attempt to get the film made, years and years ago, and it =
was deeply moving to bask in his accomplishments with him.

The marquee event, of course, featured a twin bill starring Matt, himself. =
First, Matt held a deeply introspective conversation with Mikey Madison, th=
e breakout star of Anora, who spoke candidly and evocatively about everythi=
ng from her early experience working under Tarantino to her remarkably brav=
e portrayal of Ani Mikheeva, the exotic dancer at the center of Sean Baker=
=E2=80=99s film. (If you haven=E2=80=99t seen Anora, please remedy the situ=
ation promptly.) Afterward, Matt welcomed Dune helmerfilmmaker Denis Villen=
euve for a riveting exchange about his filmmaking journey, his directorial =
influences, and his own inspirations. Matt=E2=80=99s conversation with Mike=
y is available now ( https://puck.news/podcast_episode/anora-actress-mikey-=
madison-plus-wicked-vs-gladiator-ii/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRI=
BERS+%2811%2F23%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2811%2F1=
6%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c=
60617da42abd12a ) on The Town, his excellent
podcast. The Denis interview will land on the feed this Wednesday.

After the event, I huddled with Dylan Byers and Ben Landy, Puck=E2=80=99s e=
xecutive editor, to watch the remainder of the much-ballyhooed but utterly =
depressing Mike Tyson-Jake Paul boxing match. By that point, the narrative =
had coalesced not around the depressing stunt of a former champ, four decad=
es past his prime, squaring off against a YouTube star. Instead, the intern=
et was aghast over Netflix=E2=80=99s inability to maintain the stream. View=
ers were experiencing outages=E2=80=94a sign, perhaps, of both Netflix=E2=
=80=99s
inexperience in live event production, but also the infrastructure-buckling=
 demand of its global audience.

If you only have time to read one article this weekend, I=E2=80=99d turn yo=
ur attention to John Ourand=E2=80=99s delightful piece on the contretemps s=
temming from the fight. About That Tyson-Paul Netflix Number=E2=80=A6 ( htt=
ps://puck.news/about-that-60-million-mike-tyson-jake-paul-netflix-ratings-n=
umber/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2811%2F23%2F24%29&utm_co=
ntent=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2811%2F16%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_a=
ction&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) homes in on =
the streamer=E2=80=99s triumphant post-fight brag stats. But the piece also=
 explains how ratings, themselves, have turned into a war zone between lega=
cy media and the well-capitalized streamers who have come for their supper.=
 The numbers surrounding the Tyson-Paul fight suggest that these forces wil=
l be competing over everything
in the coming years=E2=80=94the rights to distribute these events, of cours=
e, but also the new metrics for success. Indeed, it=E2=80=99s going to be o=
ne of the great and roiling debates of our time, and precisely what you sho=
uld expect to read about in Puck.

Have a wonderful Thanksgiving,
Jon

