          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">On Friday evening, =
I hopped into a Polestar and headed east from Beverly Hills to Hollywood fo=
r Puck=E2=80=99s first-ever Los Angeles tentpole, Stories of the Season. Mo=
nths ago, my partner <b>Matt Belloni </b>had articulated his vision for a n=
ew kind of Academy Awards season event=E2=80=94an editorially independent c=
oncept denuded of the traditional log-rolling and junket energy, and one th=
at leveraged the collective brilliance of Puck=E2=80=99s extensive partners=
hip. In particular, Matt envisioned our partners taking the stage to interv=
iew awards contenders whose work intersected with their own areas of expert=
ise. It was a brilliant idea, hiding in plain sight, and Matt immediately b=
egan manifesting it with the help of Puck=E2=80=99s experiential wizard, <b=
>Louise Johnson</b>.<br/><br/>Matt=E2=80=99s vision came to life on Friday =
evening at The Brownstone, a beautifully
rendered space off Cahuenga, a stone=E2=80=99s throw in either direction fr=
om the Hollywood Bowl and the Griffith Park Observatory. The peerless <b>La=
uren Sherman </b><u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6=
ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUV1VUcGpSV1FSa3d5a3h2bkNWTT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM=
6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3Mvc3Rvcmllcy1vZi10aGUtc2Vhc29uLXNsYXlpbmctdGhlLXNjcmVlbi8_dX=
RtX2NhbXBhaWduPVRoZStCYWNrc3RvcnkrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgxMSUyRjIzJTJGMjQlM=
jlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD1UaGUrQmFja3N0b3J5Ky0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MTElMkYx=
NiUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25cdTAwMjZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWN=
1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwiaW50ZXJuYWwiOi=
JmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjoxOTg2OTAxfQ/a4ab0d366916f31a43e959=
7e29b2cf0bbacc6951310153ad1d3b14c1fc4e286b" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-dec=
oration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">interviewed</a></u> some of th=
e industry=E2=80=99s top costume designers=E2=80=94including Loewe=E2=80=99=
s <b>Jonathan Anderson</b>, the stylist visionary behind the looks in <b>Lu=
ca</b> <b>Guadagnino</b>=E2=80=99s <i>Challengers </i>and <i>Queer</i>=E2=
=80=94about the precision and intellect that goes into the aesthetic tapest=
ry of filmmaking. The great <b>Baratunde Thurston </b><u><a href=3D"https:/=
/email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUV1VUcGpSV1=
FSa3d5a3h2bkNWTT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvZmlsbW1ha2Vycy1iZWhpb=
mQtdGhlLXllYXJzLWJlc3QtZG9jdW1lbnRhcmllcy10YWxrLXN0b3J5LWNyYWZ0Lz91dG1fY2Ft=
cGFpZ249VGhlK0JhY2tzdG9yeSstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODExJTJGMjMlMkYyNCUyOVx1MDA=
yNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PVRoZStCYWNrc3RvcnkrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgxMSUyRjE2JTJGMj=
QlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3VzdG9tZ=
XIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2YzYw=
NjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjE5ODg1NjV9/c4f6fcce5acb192a5135be3f2915e4=
818e2d715aa0d4bba74b525b090cf7049c" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-decoration:=
none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">chatted</a></u> with the season=E2=80=
=99s top documentarians about the backstories undergirding their work. (I w=
as particularly interested in the commentary from <b>Morgan Neville</b>, wh=
ose <i>Piece by Piece </i>I had just watched with my family a few nights ea=
rlier, and <b>Matt Tyrnauer</b>, the acclaimed director behind <i>Carville:=
 Winning Is Everything, Stupid</i>. More than 20 years ago, Matt was my bos=
s when I interned at <i>Vanity Fair</i>.)<br/><br/>Meanwhile, <b>Peter Hamb=
y </b>helmed a starry panel featuring <b>Zoe Salda=C3=B1a</b>, <b>Peter Sar=
sgaard</b>, and <b>Jeremy Strong</b>, three leading acting-awards contender=
s this season. Strong, who stars as a young <b>Roy Cohn </b>in <i>The Appre=
ntice</i>, was particularly poignant onstage. And I was thrilled to hear hi=
m explain his process while standing beside <b>Gabe Sherman</b>, my old
friend and the film=E2=80=99s screenwriter and producer. I fondly remembere=
d Gabe=E2=80=99s attempt to get the film made, years and years ago, and it =
was deeply moving to bask in his accomplishments with him.<br/><br/>The mar=
quee event, of course, featured a twin bill starring Matt, himself. First, =
Matt held a deeply introspective conversation with <b>Mikey Madison</b>, th=
e breakout star of <i>Anora</i>, who spoke candidly and evocatively about e=
verything from her early experience working under <b>Tarantino </b>to her r=
emarkably brave portrayal of Ani Mikheeva, the exotic dancer at the center =
of <b>Sean Baker</b>=E2=80=99s film. (If you haven=E2=80=99t seen <i>Anora<=
/i>, please remedy the situation promptly.) Afterward, Matt welcomed <i>Dun=
e </i>helmerfilmmaker <b>Denis Villeneuve </b>for a riveting exchange about=
 his filmmaking journey, his directorial influences, and his own inspiratio=
ns. Matt=E2=80=99s conversation with Mikey is <u><a href=3D"https://email.p=
uck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUV1VUcGpSV1FSa3d5a3=
h2bkNWTT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvcG9kY2FzdF9lcGlzb2RlL2Fub3JhL=
WFjdHJlc3MtbWlrZXktbWFkaXNvbi1wbHVzLXdpY2tlZC12cy1nbGFkaWF0b3ItaWkvP3V0bV9j=
YW1wYWlnbj1UaGUrQmFja3N0b3J5Ky0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MTElMkYyMyUyRjI0JTI5XHU=
wMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9VGhlK0JhY2tzdG9yeSstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODExJTJGMTYlMk=
YyNCUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWxfYWN0aW9uXHUwMDI2dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1jdXN0b=
21lci5pb1x1MDAyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImludGVybmFsIjoiZjZj=
NjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MTk4OTE4Nn0/db32739c04f0c9ea1b66c935757=
168cd6d40665a34f801b67885ea52440082c8" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-decorati=
on:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">available now</a></u> on <i>The Tow=
n</i>, his excellent podcast. The Denis interview will land on the feed thi=
s Wednesday. <br/><br/>After the event, I huddled with <b>Dylan Byers </b>a=
nd <b>Ben Landy</b>, Puck=E2=80=99s executive editor, to watch the remainde=
r of the much-ballyhooed but utterly depressing <b>Mike Tyson</b>-<b>Jake P=
aul </b>boxing match. By that point, the narrative had coalesced not around=
 the depressing stunt of a former champ, four decades past his prime, squar=
ing off against a YouTube star. Instead, the internet was aghast over Netfl=
ix=E2=80=99s inability to maintain the stream. Viewers were experiencing ou=
tages=E2=80=94a sign, perhaps, of both Netflix=E2=80=99s
inexperience in live event production, but also the infrastructure-buckling=
 demand of its global audience.<br/><br/>If you only have time to read one =
article this weekend, I=E2=80=99d turn your attention to <b>John Ourand</b>=
=E2=80=99s delightful piece on the contretemps stemming from the fight. <u>=
<i><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2U=
ktxclJLZ0dUV1VUcGpSV1FSa3d5a3h2bkNWTT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3Mv=
YWJvdXQtdGhhdC02MC1taWxsaW9uLW1pa2UtdHlzb24tamFrZS1wYXVsLW5ldGZsaXgtcmF0aW5=
ncy1udW1iZXIvP3V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1UaGUrQmFja3N0b3J5Ky0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MT=
ElMkYyMyUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9VGhlK0JhY2tzdG9yeSstK1NVQlNDUklCR=
VJTKyUyODExJTJGMTYlMkYyNCUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWxfYWN0aW9uXHUwMDI2=
dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1jdXN0b21lci5pb1x1MDAyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSI=
sImludGVybmFsIjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MTk4ODQ5OX0/53e5ce=
99f6fee99bfe301e78f42ee351f7095d8b3135a1eb66faa22d0619f99a" style=3D"color:=
#d40000;text-decoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">About That Tys=
on-Paul Netflix Number=E2=80=A6</a></i></u> homes in on the streamer=E2=80=
=99s triumphant post-fight brag stats. But the piece also explains how rati=
ngs, themselves, have turned into a war zone between legacy media and the w=
ell-capitalized streamers who have come for their supper. The numbers surro=
unding the Tyson-Paul fight suggest that these forces will be competing ove=
r <i>everything
</i>in the coming years=E2=80=94the rights to distribute these events, of c=
ourse, but also the new metrics for success. Indeed, it=E2=80=99s going to =
be one of the great and roiling debates of our time, and precisely what you=
 should expect to read about in Puck.<br/><br/>Have a wonderful Thanksgivin=
g,<br/>Jon<br/></td>
